3.01	Nsima	Nshima	Nshima or nsima or Bidia is a cornmeal product and a staple food in Zambia, Malawi and the Kasai Oriental and Kasai Occidental provinces of the Democratic Republic of Congo. It is made from ground maize (corn) flour known locally as mealie-meal. Nshima is very similar to ugali or posho of East Africa, sadza of Zimbabwe, pap of South Africa and fufu of West Africa.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/Nsima_Relishes.JPG/300px-Nsima_Relishes.JPG
